## 4. Nuxt Folder Structure

Map to `pages/` (file-based routing):

```
pages/
  index.vue
  meetings-events.vue
  dining.vue
  amenities.vue
  privacy-policy.vue
  contact.vue
  hotel-policies.vue
  rooms/
    index.vue
    [slug].vue
  blog/
    index.vue
    [slug].vue
  offers/
    index.vue
    [slug].vue
```

**Mapping:** `pages/foo.vue` → `/foo`. `pages/rooms/index.vue` → `/rooms`. `pages/rooms/[slug].vue` → `/rooms/:slug`. Nested folders define path prefixes; dynamic params match segment names.

## 5. Slug Rules (Strict)

- Lowercase only.
- **kebab-case** (hyphens between words).
- No spaces; no arbitrary special characters (stick to `[a-z0-9-]`).
- **Unique per collection** (unique `rooms.slug`, unique `blog_posts.slug`, unique `offers.slug`).
- **Authoritative in CMS**; frontend does not invent slugs for production content.

**Examples:** `deluxe-king-room`, `premium-twin-room`, `family-room`.

## 6. CMS Compatibility

**Idea:** Routes are **collection + slug**; adapters translate API → normalized models. Same components regardless of Strapi vs Directus.

### Collections (conceptual)

| Collection | Route | Key fields (minimum) |
|------------|-------|----------------------|
| `rooms` | `/rooms`, `/rooms/[slug]` | `slug`, `title`, `content` (+ media, SEO as per project) |
| `blog_posts` | `/blog`, `/blog/[slug]` | `slug`, `title`, `content` |
| `offers` | `/offers`, `/offers/[slug]` | `slug`, `title`, `content` (+ booking benefit fields in **data**, not in URL) |

**Mapping:**

- `/rooms/[slug]` → filter/query `rooms` where `slug === params.slug` (detail); listing queries all published rooms (with pagination as needed).
- `/blog/[slug]` → `blog_posts` by `slug`.
- `/offers/[slug]` → `offers` by `slug`.

Use **slug as stable public identifier**; internal numeric IDs stay in adapters/API only if required.

## 7. Do’s and Don’ts

**Do:**

- Group entities under parent routes (`/rooms`, `/blog`, `/offers`).
- Keep paths short and meaningful; one pattern per content type.
- Reuse this tree across hotel projects; vary only static page set if needed.
- Pass links and canonical URLs from data/layout/composables—**not** hardcoded in presentational components.

**Don’t:**

- Flatten room URLs (e.g. `/deluxe-room` instead of `/rooms/deluxe-room`).
- Mix naming styles (camelCase paths, random `/page-2` blobs).
- Add deep nesting without a clear domain reason (e.g. `/hotel/rooms/category/slug` unless explicitly required).
- Encode CMS vendor or internal IDs in public URLs.

## 8. Future Scalability

Optional later routes (same static-vs-dynamic rules):

- `/gallery`, `/location`, `/faqs` — typically **static** pages or **static + optional `[slug]`** if galleries/FAQ become collections.

**Do not implement until product asks**; current list/detail pattern already extends cleanly.

## 9. Final Principles

- **Consistency** over ad-hoc flexibility.
- **Agreed structure** over one-off creative URLs.
- **CMS-driven** slugs and copy; UI remains presentational.
- **Reusable** across all hotel Nuxt projects in this portfolio.
